<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SINGLE REDUCTION, SINGLE DRIVE AXLES: EATON - ASSEMBLE -
        PINION OIL SEAL AND YOKE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>PINION OIL SEAL AND YOKE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With pinion bearing preload adjustment complete, install oil seal. Use a press and properly
                sized sleeve to prevent distortion or contact with seal lips during installation (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401229">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401229" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401229" filename="../figg14/G1401229.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 29. Install Oil Seal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure yoke is clean and dry. Install yoke and nut (or nut and washer on some models).
                Tighten nut. Refer to the
                <hotlnk document="s14012_32.xml" xrefid="hl1401203">TORQUE CHART
                    <xref refid="hl1401203"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>After tightening nut, recheck pinion bearing rolling torque, then proceed with pinion
                        installation in carrier.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
